remember them champions of humanity stanford university search titles search all text home king papers project liberation curriculum king resources news and events community clayborne carson about the institute remember them champions of humanity the liberation curriculum lc initiative of the martin luther king jr research and education institute developed a high school curriculum to accompany the remember them champions of humanity monument created by sculptor mario chiodo and scheduled to be installed in the new henry j kaiser sculpture park in fox square downtown oakland ca the monument features 25 humanitarians who have inspired chiodo through their courage perseverance education sacrifice and a sincere desire to strive for a better life for all artist's statement rt website the lc curriculum is aligned with ca content standards and is accompanied by biographies of the 25 humanitarians it was piloted in schools in the oakland unified school district ousd in spring 2009 the instructional video below was filmed in east oakland school of the arts illustrating the teaching of the curriculum to an urban high school class thanks to teachers fatima ghatela and aryn bowman for facilitating the filming in their classroom download the curriculum here download the biographies for the 25 humanitarians here 00 00 00 00 2009 flowplayer ltd popular topics letter from birmingham jail 1963 march on washington for jobs and freedom montgomery bus boycott 1955 1956 nonviolent resistance home about us contact us copyright information the king center rss
